HEADWORD: Patamar
<hw>Pat"a*mar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A vessel resembling a grab, used in
the coasting trade of Bombay and Ceylon.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>pattemar</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

